<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1303,1327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of its collector, Manuel Zumbado of 
<collectionCode box="[939,1009,1302,1326]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/931n-s1te" name="National Biodiversity Institute, Costa Rica" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">INBio</collectionCode>
and specialist on Costa Rican Diptera (
<bibRefCitation author="Zumbado" box="[158,335,1338,1362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Zumbado, M. (2006) Dipteros de Costa Rica y la America tropical, Editorial INBio [Instituto Nacional de Biodiversidad (Costa Rica)], 267 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Zumbado 
<number box="[275,335,1338,1362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), including their mimicry.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,258,1470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1374,1399]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Discussion.</emphasis>
In this species, the bright blue base of the pronotum gives a stronger visual impression of a separate red head, and the greenish blue scutellum is striking. As with 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1040,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opitzi">
<emphasis box="[889,1040,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Agrilus opitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Waterhouse" authorityName="Waterhouse" box="[1094,1384,1410,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatus">
<emphasis box="[1094,1243,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. dimidiatus</emphasis>
Waterhouse
</taxonomicName>
, this species lacks silvery setae on the sides of abdominal ventrite 
<number box="[836,850,1446,1470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
